The paper introduces a new family of combinatorial simplicial complexes motivated by theoretical distributed computing, specifically the immediate snapshot read/write shared memory communication model. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Graph Theory (cs.GT), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
